SWISS DAYBOOK: UBS Board Meeting, Holcim CEO, Swiss GDP Estimate

-- B y   C a r o l y n   B a n d e l
-- 
2011-09-20T06:01:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/swiss-daybook-ubs-board-meeting-holcim-ceo-swiss-gdp-estimate.html
UBS AG (UBSN) ’s directors will meet in
 Singapore  later this week following the lender’s disclosure of a
$2.3 billion loss from unauthorized trading, according to two
people with knowledge of the situation.  The board will discuss the loss and review possible
management changes, said one of the people who declined to be
identified because the discussions are private. Officials at the
Zurich-based bank declined to comment.  EQUITIES:
*UBS CEO Oswald Gruebel was informed about trader Kweku
Adoboli’s losses on Wednesday Sept. 14 at 4 p.m., Tages-Anzeiger
reported
*Holcim said Bernard Fontana from steelmaker Aperam will take
over as chief executive officer when Markus Akermann retires
*Comet Holding said it plans to introduce short-time working in
its plasma control technologies operations in Flamatt from next
month because of weak demand
*ABB will work with Eskom Holdings to build two solar
photovoltaic  power plants ,  Business Report  said
*ABB was rated new “underweight” at Grupo Santander
*Basilea was raised to “hold” from “underperform” at
Jefferies  ECONOMY/GOVERNMENT:
*The Swiss State Secretariat for Economic Affairs lowered growth
estimates for this year and next
*Swiss exports dropped 7 percent in August from July
*Switzerland to sell three-month bills
*Swiss parliament holds session in Bern  MARKETS:
*The SMI dropped 1.7 percent to 5,360.56
*The SPI dropped 1.7 percent to 4,895.18
*The Stoxx Europe 600 Index dropped 2.3 percent to 224.96
*The MSCI Asia-Pacific Index dropped 1.1 percent at 7:57 a.m.
Zurich time
*Euro-franc traded at 1.2064 at 7:57 a.m. Zurich time  To contact the reporter on this story:
